article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 73, UC Davis 54
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Alex Harris scored 15 points off the bench and Glenn Turner added 12 points and 10 rebounds as UC Santa Barbara snapped a three-game losing streak with a 73-54 victory over UC Davis. The Gauchos (7-11) shot 55.8 percent, which included 7-for-13 shooting from behind the 3-point line. UC Davis (6-15) made just one of 17 shots from behind the arc and finished at 37 percent overall. Thomas Juillerat went 6-of-9 to lead the Aggies with 17 points. Michael Chambers hit his first four shots to send UC Santa Barbara out to a 25-11 lead. He finished with 11 points. The Gauchos led 32-20 at halftime, and extended their lead to 47-26 after Chris Devine scored seven of his 14 points in the first six minutes of the second half.
